<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/12395050-neal-mcgrath">Neal McGrath </a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I would read Celine in the order published.It&apos;s all about the style with Celine and if you start at the beginning,you can see how he develops.<br/><br/>For many<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">â¦more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I would read Celine in the order published.It's all about the style with Celine and if you start at the beginning,you can see how he develops.<br /><br />For many people he gets more chaotic and wild as he progresses(I haven't read past Guignols Band yet-his third book),so Journey To The End Of The Night is his most accessible book,but also regarded by many as his best.<br /><br />The Perfect place to start,and if you like it-carry on!!!<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
