           <span class="uitext reviewText">Pj Perez, Jerry Misko, Matt Keleman</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer19897585" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer382383834074839833">The master of the ellipse, Celine recounts his tragi-comic career as a youth and doctor in the Paris suburb of Montemartre. If you know Celine, this is his darkest but, in my opinion , most beautifully and vividly written novel. He spins and sputters off into an inner world that has great clarity concerning the surrounding outer world, without any great ability to relate properly to it.I just found myself relating to like my own. If you are new to Celine, think of it as Bukowski meets Moulin Rou</span>
  <span id="freeText382383834074839833" style="display:none">The master of the ellipse, Celine recounts his tragi-comic career as a youth and doctor in the Paris suburb of Montemartre. If you know Celine, this is his darkest but, in my opinion , most beautifully and vividly written novel. He spins and sputters off into an inner world that has great clarity concerning the surrounding outer world, without any great ability to relate properly to it.I just found myself relating to like my own. If you are new to Celine, think of it as Bukowski meets Moulin Rouge. While also a fan of Journey to the End of Night, I personally find this one to be the better novel. Great with red wine (or absinthe) and a cigar.</span>
  <a data-text-id="382383834074839833" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
